summary:
Welcomes the conclusion of the Status of Forces Agreement with the Government of the Republic of South Sudan and calls on the host government to comply with its obligations.

 Stresses the need for international partners to work closely with the Government of the Republic of South Sudan to ensure international assistance.
The Security Council:

requests the UNMISS to deliver prioritized support reflecting South Sudan's peacebuilding needs and priorities, in line with the South Sudan Development Plan;
 underscores the need for close cooperation between parties to avoid duplication of effort; 
requests the Secretary-General's Special Representative to represent the UN system in international assistance mechanisms;
encourages exploring ideas from the Senior Advisory Group report on civilian capacity;
requests utilizing co-location of mission components with national counterparts and seeking opportunities for local procurement;
demands full compliance with the UN's zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse;
reaffirms the importance of gender expertise and training;
requests addressing HIV-related needs and incorporating prevention, treatment, and care programs;
requests UNMISS to support preparations for credible national elections in 2015; 
and decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
